window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>A Falling Stars stand-alone novel from <i>NYT</i> and <i>USA Today</i> best-selling author A. L. Jackson....&nbsp;</p> <p>A single mother.</p> <p>An up-and-coming drummer with a sordid past.&nbsp;</p> <p>Their paths never should have crossed.&nbsp;</p> <p>But when a senseless crime rocks Mia West's entire world, she agrees to spend the summer hiding out at her rock-star brother's mansion in Savannah until the storm blows over.&nbsp;</p> <p>What she never expected was the gorgeous, brooding drummer living in the guest house.&nbsp;</p> <p>His darkness a lure.&nbsp;</p> <p>His gaze a trap.&nbsp;</p> <p>She knows better than to go after what will hurt her most.&nbsp;</p> <p>Leif Godwin has two focuses in his life: his band, Carolina George, and seeking retribution for what was stolen from him.</p> <p>Mia was never supposed to be a part of the equation.</p> <p>Her eyes an appeal.</p> <p>Her body a temptation.</p> <p>Touching her is nothing but a sin.&nbsp;</p> <p>But will loving her destroy them all....</p>"; 
